In Google Cloud Datastore, to retrieve the value associated with a particular key, you need to perform a query or a direct lookup using that key. Here's how you can retrieve a value using a key in Google Cloud Datastore:

1. **Using a Direct Lookup:**

Assuming you have the key of the entity you want to retrieve, you can directly fetch the entity using the key.

```javascript
const { Datastore } = require('@google-cloud/datastore');

// Creates a client
const datastore = new Datastore();

// Define the key
const key = datastore.key(['KindName', 'EntityId']);

// Fetch the entity using the key
datastore.get(key)
  .then(([entity]) => {
    if (entity) {
      console.log('Entity:', entity);
    } else {
      console.log('Entity not found.');
    }
  })
  .catch(err => {
    console.error('Error:', err);
  });
```

Replace `'KindName'` with the name of your entity kind and `'EntityId'` with the ID or name of the specific entity you're looking for.

2. **Using a Query:**

If you have certain properties to filter by, you can use a query to retrieve the value. For example, if you want to retrieve an entity by a property named `propertyName`:

```javascript
const { Datastore } = require('@google-cloud/datastore');

// Creates a client
const datastore = new Datastore();

// Define the query
const query = datastore.createQuery('KindName').filter('propertyName', '=', 'desiredValue');

// Run the query
datastore.runQuery(query)
  .then(([entities]) => {
    if (entities.length > 0) {
      console.log('Entities:', entities);
    } else {
      console.log('No entities found.');
    }
  })
  .catch(err => {
    console.error('Error:', err);
  });
```

Replace `'KindName'` with the name of your entity kind, `'propertyName'` with the property you want to filter by, and `'desiredValue'` with the value you're searching for.

Remember to replace `'KindName'` and `'propertyName'` with the actual names in your data model. Also, ensure you have the `@google-cloud/datastore` package installed in your project using `npm install @google-cloud/datastore`.

