Passing Bearer tokens to a page inside an iframe involves ensuring that the parent page (the one containing the iframe) securely communicates the token to the iframe. Here are a few methods you can use:

1. **URL Parameters:**
   Although passing tokens in URLs is generally discouraged, if you have no other options, you can pass a token as a URL parameter to the iframe source URL. However, be aware that this method is less secure, as URLs can be logged, shared, and may end up in browser history.

   Parent Page:
   ```javascript
   const iframeUrl = `https://youriframe.com?token=${encodeURIComponent(bearerToken)}`;
   iframeElement.src = iframeUrl;
   ```

   In Iframe Page:
   ```javascript
   const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
   const token = urlParams.get('token');
   ```

2. **Window.postMessage:**
   Use the `postMessage` method to safely communicate data between the parent and iframe windows, even across different origins. This method allows you to pass data without exposing it directly in the URL.

   Parent Page:
   ```javascript
   iframeElement.contentWindow.postMessage(bearerToken, 'https://youriframe.com');
   ```

   In Iframe Page:
   ```javascript
   window.addEventListener('message', event => {
     if (event.origin === 'https://parentpage.com') {
       const token = event.data;
     }
   });
   ```

3. **Cookies:**
   If the parent page and the iframe are on the same domain, you can set a cookie containing the token on the parent page and access it in the iframe. This approach offers better security compared to URL parameters.

   Parent Page:
   ```javascript
   document.cookie = `token=${bearerToken}`;
   ```

   In Iframe Page:
   ```javascript
   const token = document.cookie.split('; ').find(row => row.startsWith('token=')).split('=')[1];
   ```

Choose the method that best suits your use case while considering security implications. If possible, avoid exposing sensitive tokens to the client side whenever possible and opt for server-side communication with Cloud Run or other services.

